thumb|upright=1.5|garden of gethsemane gethsemane ( , gethsēmanē ; , gat-šmânim ; , gaḏ šmānê , lit . " oil press " ) is a garden at the foot of the mount of olives in jerusalem , most famous as the place where jesus prayed and his disciples slept the night before jesus ' crucifixion .

biblical food & drink : the name gethsemane comes from gath - shemen , hebrew for oil press , probably one for this fruit

